  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which China companies are the biggest exporters to USA?",
  "response": "Several Chinese companies are among the largest exporters to the United States, spanning industries such as electronics, manufacturing, and trade. While specific data on individual company exports can vary, the following companies are prominent exporters from China to the U.S.:\n\n1. **Foxconn (Hon Hai Precision Industry Co.)**  \n   - A major manufacturer of electronics, Foxconn produces devices for companies like Apple (e.g., iPhones), Dell, and Sony. It is one of the largest exporters of electronics to the U.S.\n\n2. **Huawei Technologies**  \n   - Despite U.S. sanctions in recent years, Huawei has been a significant exporter of telecommunications equipment, smartphones, and other consumer electronics.\n\n3. **Lenovo Group**  \n   - One of the world's largest PC manufacturers, Lenovo exports laptops, desktops, and other computing devices to the U.S.\n\n4. **BYD Company**  \n   - A leading manufacturer of electric vehicles (EVs), batteries, and renewable energy products, BYD exports EV components and other products to the U.S.\n\n5. **Haier Group (now part of Haier Smart Home)**  \n   - A major exporter of home appliances like refrigerators, washing machines, and air conditioners, Haier is one of the largest appliance manufacturers globally.\n\n6. **ZTE Corporation**  \n   - A telecommunications equipment and smartphone manufacturer, ZTE exports network infrastructure and mobile devices to the U.S.\n\n7. **Hisense**  \n   - A leading exporter of consumer electronics, including TVs, refrigerators, and air conditioners, to the U.S.\n\n8. **Sinopec and PetroChina**  \n   - Both companies are major exporters of chemicals, plastics, and petroleum-related products to the U.S.\n\n9. **Li & Fung (trading company)**  \n   - Although headquartered in Hong Kong, Li & Fung plays a significant role in exporting textiles, apparel, and consumer goods from China to the U.S.\n\n10. **Alibaba Group (via its e-commerce platforms)**  \n    - Through platforms like AliExpress, Alibaba facilitates the export of a wide range of goods, including electronics, apparel, and consumer products, to the U.S.\n\nThese companies represent the diversity of China\u2019s export economy, which includes both state-owned enterprises and private companies. Additionally, many smaller manufacturers and suppliers in China export goods to the U.S. through intermediaries or e-commerce platforms.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
